254
00:19:15,820 --> 00:19:18,820
At first I was stressed to death, so I was hiding it from her.

255
00:19:18,820 --> 00:19:20,240
But in the end, she wasn't angry.

256
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:23,740
If I knew this, I wouldn't have wasted time sleeping over and this and that person's houses.

257
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:27,165
Whose houses have you slept over?

258
00:19:27,940 --> 00:19:29,980
Come on. Don't be mad.

259
00:19:29,980 --> 00:19:33,580
I was laying around over at P'No's house. And I also played games over at P'Job's house.

260
00:19:33,580 --> 00:19:36,280
Once Ai'Ley went to sleep, I just went back home. That's all.

261
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:38,480
Next time, come and sleep over at my house.

262
00:19:39,020 --> 00:19:42,020
I don't want to. Your house is also far.

263
00:19:42,020 --> 00:19:44,840
Also, it'd be really late and you'd have to drop me off, too.

264
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,380
There are no buses either.

265
00:19:46,380 --> 00:19:49,400
If I was to sleep there, the only option would be to spend the night there.

266
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:55,360
But I'm at ease now. Because either way, now I won't get killed by my little sister.

267
00:19:57,320 --> 00:20:01,220
Fine. Then I think I'll buy a room as well.

268
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:06,200
What are you going to buy a room for?

269
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:09,380
You already have a house. You also already have a car.

270
00:20:09,380 --> 00:20:11,660
For what crazy reason would you need to buy a room?

271
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:16,400
So we can do something more conveniently.

272
00:20:17,947 --> 00:20:19,547
Are...

273
00:20:19,547 --> 00:20:23,155
you... talking about dirty stuff?

274
00:20:24,580 --> 00:20:27,920
That's right. Right now, it's not very convenient.

275
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,640
How is it not convenient?

276
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:35,240
My mom didn't even say anything about me staying over at your house.

277
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:37,120
But if you're bored, you can come to my house!

278
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:39,040
My mom doesn't mind.

279
00:20:39,740 --> 00:20:43,940
If I go, do you think the people in your house won't know...

280
00:20:43,940 --> 00:20:46,060
that we…

281
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:50,300
That's true...

282
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:53,900
If I were to imagine my mom hearing me...

283
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:55,100
I get goosebumps!

284
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:57,840
Mom would definitely smash the door down to come in!

285
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,920
But Ai'Tin,

286
00:21:00,820 --> 00:21:04,460
are... you really going to buy a room just for that reason?

287
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:09,020
Khun Chai Tin is definitely not ordinary, huh?

288
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:12,040
Not just that.

289
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:15,180
I also want freedom, too.

290
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:21,220
Then... why are you just buying it now when you just started dating me?

291
00:21:27,980 --> 00:21:30,680
At that time, I wanted to have some existence in that house, too.

292
00:21:36,580 --> 00:21:39,340
You don't have to worry, all right? Forget those people in that house!

293
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:41,260
You have me now.

294
00:21:42,020 --> 00:21:45,160
If there's a day I ever meet your brother, I'll also punch him in the face for you, too.

295
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:48,100
You said it already, all right?

296
00:21:49,220 --> 00:21:53,160
Trust me. Someone like me is a man of my word.

297
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:13,120
[Personal Information]

298
00:22:40,740 --> 00:22:44,300
It's time for your brother to meet him.

299
00:22:59,740 --> 00:23:01,260
What is it?

300
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,320
It's about the internship.

301
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:18,760
Didn't I already tell your older brother that I'm not letting you do it?

302
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:22,900
Let's talk about this when the university tells you to do it.

303
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:24,640
Then why that…

304
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:29,320
Why can P'Tul do it but I can't?

305
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:34,260
Because you and your older brother are not the same.

306
00:23:34,260 --> 00:23:37,660
How are we not the same? Aren't we both Medthanan?

307
00:23:39,547 --> 00:23:43,580
Because your older brother has to shoulder all the responsibility and burdens instead of me.

308
00:23:43,580 --> 00:23:45,640
But you're not the one.

309
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:52,740
Dad, you're saying that like I'm not your child.

310
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,720
I never said anything like that.

311
00:24:05,020 --> 00:24:07,400
And what if I asked to live somewhere else?

312
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:14,920
It's up to you.

313
00:24:38,420 --> 00:24:42,100
Just looking at your face and I already know that you must not have gotten what you wanted, huh, Tin?

314
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:47,460
I already told you. You can't means you can't.

315
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:56,380
You're the one who told Dad, right?

316
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,920
Look at what you're saying...

317
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:02,720
Anything that Dad has already decided on... I also can't do anything about it.

318
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:07,300
There's something on this earth that you can't do?

319
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:09,420
There's plenty.

320
00:25:09,420 --> 00:25:14,020
Such as the matter of... making my little brother go back to being adorable like before.

321
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:18,240
That probably will never happen.

322
00:25:20,540 --> 00:25:23,800
And don't forget to bring your friend and introduce him to me, too.

323
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,900
Damn it.

324
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:02,660
He no longer exists.

325
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:06,880
That stupid little brother...

326
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,980
can no longer exist.

327
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:24,760
Brother Tul. Brother Tul, you have to believe me.

328
00:26:24,820 --> 00:26:27,400
I really didn't mess with drugs!

329
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,540
Everyone looks at me badly now, Brother!

330
00:26:29,540 --> 00:26:31,640
But I really didn't do it.

331
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:39,440
Even if other people don't believe it, it's all right.

332
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:42,200
But you have to believe me, Brother. All right?

333
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,320
You have to believe me, all right?

334
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:49,800
Right now, Mom and Dad already hate me.

335
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,580
But I don't care, Brother.

336
00:26:54,580 --> 00:26:56,860
As long as you believe me, that's enough.

337
00:26:56,860 --> 00:27:00,080
Of course, I believe you. I believe you.

338
00:27:10,300 --> 00:27:13,080
Because I'm the one who made you like this.

339
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:21,260
What do you mean?

340
00:27:21,260 --> 00:27:23,480
This is not funny.

341
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:26,260
Do you think I'm joking?

342
00:27:26,260 --> 00:27:30,240
I'm the one who put you at that party.

343
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:33,480
I'm the one who called the news reporters there.

344
00:27:33,480 --> 00:27:35,960
I'm the one who ordered you to be on the news there.

345
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:39,040
I'm the one who ruined your life.

346
00:27:46,020 --> 00:27:47,340
I don't believe it.

347
00:27:47,340 --> 00:27:49,140
You're just joking, right?

348
00:27:50,660 --> 00:27:52,000
You...You're drunk, right?

349
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,940
I told you not to drink too much alcohol! It's not good!

350
00:27:53,940 --> 00:27:56,280
Just how much longer are you going to be stupid, Ai'Tin?!

351
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:58,300
I've never loved you at all!

352
00:27:58,300 --> 00:28:00,200
I've wanted you dead since the day you were born!

353
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:03,240
If there was no you, your mom, and your grandmother,

354
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:05,680
then I wouldn't have to experience this kind of shit!

355
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:08,580
So now I'll ruin your life, too.

356
00:28:12,060 --> 00:28:13,900
I hate you!

357
00:29:03,460 --> 00:29:05,720
You can hurt anyone,

358
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:10,780
but don't hurt my important person.

359
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:15,400
It can't be Can.

360
00:29:39,610 --> 00:29:43,510
[K'Tin]

361
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:52,180
Hello.

362
00:29:52,180 --> 00:29:54,980
I want to know your former master's weakness.

363
00:29:57,220 --> 00:29:59,840
We've already made an agreement before, Khun Tin.

364
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:02,280
Tell me everything that you know about him.

365
00:30:03,280 --> 00:30:04,940
I can't tell you that.

366
00:30:04,940 --> 00:30:06,860
What did I order you before?

367
00:30:06,860 --> 00:30:10,100
When you came to see me last year,

368
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:16,100
I promised you that I would use my abilities to help you do your work.

369
00:30:17,800 --> 00:30:20,320
I would do everything that you ordered me to.

370
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:22,860
But that there would be one condition,

371
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:31,040
and it's that I would never do anything that would cause harm to Khun Tul.

372
00:30:32,020 --> 00:30:34,200
I will never betray Tul.

373
00:30:35,420 --> 00:30:38,060
Even though he chased you out of the house.

374
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:42,600
Yes.

375
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:49,880
Khun Tul is not as bad as you think.

376
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:54,700
Khun Tin, you're the only family of Khun Tul.

377
00:30:56,220 --> 00:30:58,180
Do you think I would believe that?

378
00:31:21,460 --> 00:31:23,580
Khun Tul never chased me out.

379
00:31:24,620 --> 00:31:27,160
I was the one who left of my own accord.

380
00:31:35,620 --> 00:31:37,900
Calm down first. All right, Vadee?

381
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:45,140
What am I going to do, P'Tul?

382
00:31:51,360 --> 00:31:54,000
What should I do?

383
00:32:01,740 --> 00:32:03,720
I have something to tell you.

384
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:17,720
I'm pregnant.

385
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:25,060
I'm pregnant, P'Tul.

386
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:51,000
You finally have the family that you wanted.

387
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,360
Thank you for keeping your promise.

388
00:32:54,360 --> 00:32:56,720
Thank you for not coming to look for me.

389
00:32:57,920 --> 00:33:01,660
I wish you happiness. That's enough for me.

390
00:33:06,500 --> 00:33:09,920
You're my entire world, Khun Tul.

391
00:33:24,580 --> 00:33:26,260
Hello, Can?

392
00:33:27,060 --> 00:33:28,600
Are you awake yet?

393
00:33:29,180 --> 00:33:31,020
I'm going out right now to pick you up.

394
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:33,600
I'm awake now...

395
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:34,900
So where are we going today?

396
00:33:34,900 --> 00:33:36,480
Where do you want to go?

397
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:38,320
I can take you anywhere.

398
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:42,000
Then let's go to your house. I miss your chef's cooking.

399
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:45,700
Oh... and I also want to watch a movie marathon, too.

400
00:33:47,620 --> 00:33:49,540
I'm not sure if my brother will be there or not.

401
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:52,800
It'll be great if he is. I'll fight him.

402
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,580
Acting like you have a chance...

403
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:57,140
You're underestimating me, Ai'Tin.

404
00:33:57,140 --> 00:34:00,600
Hurry up and come pick me up. I'm too lazy to argue with you over the phone now.

405
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:02,840
Okay. You should quickly go take a shower then.

406
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:07,360
When I shower, just three minutes and I'm done. That's all for now, all right?

407
00:34:11,680 --> 00:34:15,300
Khun Tin, the car is ready.

408
00:34:15,300 --> 00:34:16,860
Okay.

409
00:34:20,720 --> 00:34:22,320
Where is he going?

410
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:25,560
Khun Tin, do you mean Khun Tul?

411
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:28,480
He's going to Khun Vadee's house. He should be sleeping over there today.

412
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:31,640
And he also told me that today I don't need to wait for him.

413
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:48,980
Can!

414
00:34:48,980 --> 00:34:52,140
Hey! On your way back, stop by and buy some things for me, too.

415
00:34:53,240 --> 00:34:56,160
Mom... can I not buy it?

416
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:59,120
I'll forget, and I don't know what time I'll be coming back.

417
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:01,080
Mom, why don't you use Ai'Ley to go buy it?

418
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:04,240
Well, your little sister said that during this period she needs to study for her exams.

419
00:35:04,240 --> 00:35:06,800
I have to study too, Mom.

420
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:09,640
But I heard that right now you're running off to go on a trip.

421
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:14,000
Mom, how do you know that? I might just be going out to study.

422
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:18,340
You don't have any fever!

423
00:35:18,340 --> 00:35:20,540
Mom…

424
00:35:21,660 --> 00:35:28,300
Well, Cantaloupe, Mommy's sweet and lovely son, knows of the word "studying"? Yeah, right.

425
00:35:28,300 --> 00:35:32,600
Every time I see you have exams, you're always sleeping and drowning in your drool on your books.

426
00:35:32,600 --> 00:35:37,380
Mom, you should try to look at your son in a more positive way...

427
00:35:37,380 --> 00:35:40,480
This is called accepting the truth, dear.

428
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:44,240
Is there any other mom in any other house that doesn't scold their child like me?

429
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:47,320
Even when my child fails an exam, I can even accept it and still smile.

430
00:35:47,320 --> 00:35:50,760
So, anyway, on your way back, don't forget to stop by and buy me some things.

431
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:52,780
Here's the list of stuff.

432
00:35:55,700 --> 00:35:57,900
Go ahead now. Tin's already here to pick you up.

433
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:03,280
How great would it be if I had such a handsome son like you, Tin?

434
00:36:03,280 --> 00:36:06,200
Hello. I bought this for you.

435
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:10,440
Thank you, son. You're handsome and kind as well!

436
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:13,040
As for the son in this household, well...

437
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:15,720
I wanted him to go buy some things and he complains.

438
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:21,220
Let's go, dude. I have to come back early to buy things for my dearest mother.

439
00:36:21,227 --> 00:36:23,947
Such a long list.

440
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:31,660
Would it be all right to ask if I could take Can out and have him stay over tonight?

441
00:36:31,660 --> 00:36:33,340
Huh?

442
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:39,460
As for this shopping list. Don't worry.

443
00:36:39,460 --> 00:36:41,940
I'll ask someone to buy it for you.

444
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:44,600
How can you do that?

445
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:47,120
My mom asked me to buy it. I have to be the one to buy it then!

446
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:50,200
It's okay, son. It's okay. All right.

447
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:53,500
Tin, if you're the one taking Can, then I'm not worried.

448
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:57,720
Because I believe that you won't be taking Can out to loiter around somewhere.

449
00:36:57,720 --> 00:37:01,140
You guys can go now, or you won't be able to enjoy your trip in time.

450
00:37:01,140 --> 00:37:04,100
- Goodbye.
- Yes, dear. Goodbye.

451
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:06,960
Make your face look more proper!

452
00:37:06,960 --> 00:37:08,560
All right!

453
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:14,740
It would be great if I had another son who is as incredibly sweet as Tin.

454
00:37:14,740 --> 00:37:17,080
It could be that you've had one for a while already now.

455
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:19,940
Oh, my Buddha!

456
00:37:20,040 --> 00:37:20,640
You scared me!

457
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:21,800
Why are you coming up without a sound?!

458
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:05,120
Right, Ai'Tin... Lately, my mom's always "Tin this" and "Tin that."

459
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:07,300
